# Windows batch files are launched by cmd.exe, which requires CRLF line endings.
# Mark them -text so git stores the bytes verbatim (no LF normalization). This keeps
# the committed blob CRLF, which is exactly what raw.githubusercontent.com serves and
# what users download and run — an LF-only .bat can misbehave in cmd's header parsing.
*.bat -text
*.cmd -text
